    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-23T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2331/228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-23T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 23, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>546. Reference Embassy’s telegram no. 668, of December 9. Please ascertain
                    whether Peruvian Government is agreeable to issuance of public notice of
                    intention to negotiate a trade agreement with Peru on Monday, December 29.<note
                        n="76" xml:id="d448fn76">The public notice was issued on December 29; see
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, January 3, 1942, p.
                        22.</note>
                </p>
                <p>For list of products to accompany public notice on which this country will
                    consider granting concessions to Peru, refer to instruction no. 446, of June 6,
                        1941.<note n="77" xml:id="d448fn77">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
